  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Cut the <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into bite-sized cubes</p><p>Add the <strong>cubed potatoes</strong> to a baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong> and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Put the tray in the oven and cook for an initial 20 min or until starting to crisp</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1662397147138-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1662397147138-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1662397147138-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1662397147138-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1662397147138-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>salmon fillets </strong>to the pan (skin-side down) with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper </strong>and cook for 2 min on each side until sealed but not cooked through</p><p>Carefully peel the skin off the salmon and discard it, then cut the <strong>salmon fillets</strong> in half</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1662397156291-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1662397156291-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1662397156291-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1662397156291-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1662397156291-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Dust your work surface with a generous sprinkling of <strong>flour</strong></p><p>Unwrap the <strong>puff pastry</strong> and roll it out to approx. 0.5cm thickness with a <strong>rolling pin </strong>and cut into 4 <span class=\"text-danger\">[8] </span>squares</p><p>Place 2 <strong>salmon pieces </strong>side-by-side onto each piece of <strong>pastry </strong>and spoon most of the<strong> pesto</strong> over the salmon<strong> </strong>(save the rest for later!)</p><p>Brush a little <strong>milk </strong>around the edges of the <strong>salmon-topped pastry square</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1662397161016-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1662397161016-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1662397161016-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1662397161016-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1662397161016-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Top each <strong>salmon-topped pastry square</strong> with another <strong>pastry square </strong>and seal the open ends together by pressing the edges down with a fork</p><p>Add the parcels to a baking tray and brush the tops of them with<strong> milk</strong></p><p>Sprinkle the parcels with the <strong>nigella seeds </strong>and put the tray in the oven for 20-25 minutes or until golden and cooked through – this is your <strong>pesto</strong> <strong>salmon en croûte</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1662397178547-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1662397178547-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1662397178547-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1662397178547-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1662397178547-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst the salmon en croûte is cooking, peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Once the potatoes are starting to crisp, remove them from the oven and add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong></p><p>Give it a good mix up then return to the oven for 4-5 min or until the potatoes are golden and crispy</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1662397175236-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1662397175236-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1662397175236-x700.jpg",
